caption: My wife and I try to go here at least once every two weeks.  We have never been disappointed and plan on introducing the place to many of our friends and family.

vietnamese food and the scene here is above par. Honestly my favorite evening place. The service was sociable and attentive. This place has an awesome feel to it. Makes me feel like I am back in Tucson.
Good location for tasty Vietnamese food. I'll return friends next time.
A preferred spot for vietnamese food. super savory. i see why this place has a lot of great reviews.
Vietnamese food at this place - super tasty. Service is always nice even when they have a full house. The bill was average for the menu.

At the risk of turning my 10 mins into 15, this place is the BEST pho place in LA.  Why?  It's because they don't skimp like all the "savvy pho restaurants" do.  They give you 2 slices of lime.  They give you more bean sprouts than you need …

Their broth is really good, and their noodles are the best, and they always go above and beyond to meet my requests. Best pho spot on the west side!! And I’ve tried them all. Very reasonably priced, support this small family business! See you next week! :-)
A favorite place for delicious Vietnamese food. Filled me up. This place has a great design. They have so many great reviews for a reason.

One of my preferred spots for tasty Vietnamese food. Great place to chill, get away, eat some good food. Had a sister come into town and asked me to take her here again. Prices are decent for the quality. Food is like a restaurant in Louisville I liked.

Vietnamese food and service here is great. Service is always super even when they have a full house. The service was friendly and sociable. Prices are appropriate for the quality. Not close to my job, I wish it was.
One of my fav spots for quality vietnamese food. This place is absolutely outstanding. The staff was very friendly and kind. Prices were appropriate.

Great service. Went on a Saturday around noon. Quick service. The bowl was a regular and still quite large. Plenty of meat and noodles. Broth was nice. The pork sausage spring rolls were surprisingly delicious.
Vietnamese food and the scene at this location is super good. Everyone at our table was very satisfied. This place has a great atmosphere.
Pork banh Mi was dry and bland. Near more pho broth and sambal and extra daikon .
love the flavor! Very tasty Thank you!! PHO FEVER BISTRO is the best and my favorite!
Excellent Vietnamese food. Tons of revuews already discuss the very good quality food so I won't focus too much on that. I had the beef salad starter, bok pho, and a side of garlic bok choy.
Really good customer service!
Authentic

The chicken in vegan broth was amazing. The sprimg rolls are good. If the Banh mi is a knockout next time I return they'll keep the 5 stars. For now the service and food was perfect for this little hole in the wall
Spring rolls are delicious, pho is solid, the owners are very friendly. After moving up from Orange County and being spoiled by Garden Grove, this is a great Vietnamese find for the west side :)

This restaurant has a very special place in my heart. My sister brought me to this restaurant and I absolutely fell in love with it. I had never tried Vietnamese before and I really appreciated the servers in recommending and suggesting …

I LOVE THIS PLACE, the food is amazing. My goto is the Chicken breast soup with noodles. Best plate if you want to feel full but light. The owner is super friendly and over all every vist it is a good one. HIGHLY RECOMMEND TO EVERYONE
Delicious flavorful and aromatic with a reasonable amount of salt  Enjoy authentic pho !
The only non-Americanized pho restaurant in Santa Monica. This is my go to spot for pho in SM.
This place was so highly recommend by a friend/coworker.  But it is just "okay" in my opinion

Local neighborhood Vietnamese pho shop. Food is delightfully homestyle and very delicious. Great calamari dish, really flavorful and well paired with the lightly fried onions strands, which you don't find elsewhere.

First time here and it was pretty good, the place smelled really good. The food was tasty but I've had better to be honest, I feel like this one is alil "watered down" if you know what I mean. Americanized
Good and opened all night
Love the Vietnamese noodles.
My new favorite Pho and Bahn Mi restaurant! Great service. Good portions. Easy parking. Never had a Bahn Mi with dip before - loved it! Definitely coming back!
Good pho that doesn’t skimp out on the amount of meat. Had the egg rolls which was pretty good too. Service was friendly and welcoming.

hands down the best pho i have ever had!! , just got my wisdom teeth removed and been order their pho on ubereats all week

Amazing food.
Good portion. Tasty. Only downside is the street parking is hard to find since the plaza is so small.

Great new spot for Pho on Pico at the corner of Barrington.  Had the Spicy Beef lemongrass soup - was fantastic.  Lunch Special comes with an Egg Roll (small) and Fresh brewed ice tea.  Wasn't expecting much from the outside but once inside …
They're so nice, and the food taste is nice, too.

Just got back from Vietnam and had the best Pho of my life from some little shop tucked in an alley. All I could eat and all made fresh in front of me. This place reminded me of that spot but a bigger, cleaner version with great Pho. If you want soup with noodles go get after it here.

Decent pho on the westside?? It's true!  Decent nem nuong cuon on the westside?!? Okay... THAT is truly worth a mention!  Sadly the one hiccup is parking. As in there's barely any. Be prepared to walk a block or so, and bring money for the meter.
Great little shop! Order pho number 1 or 13
Little mom and pop shop. Delicious food. My friend and I love this place so much we bought 2 of their shirts. I was surprised to find out they weren't Vietnamese lol
Good tasting broth. Kind of expensive but it is in Santa monica area. Love that they offer a vegetarian broth and there boba.

Legit some of the best food I've had in my life. Everything was so fresh. Had the beef brisket sandwich and it  just got me so excited to be able to eat something so good. Also got the rare steak pho which was great, too (but I did like the …
